17605.name: abnormal gas collection in pelvis
17605.description: Presence of gas in the pelvic region that is not normally expected, may suggest pathology.

17665.name: abnormality of entire testis
17665.description: Diffuse abnormality involving the whole testis, such as swelling, atrophy, or changed echotexture.

17879.name: adnexal lesion with high diastolic flow
17879.description: Adnexal mass demonstrating high diastolic blood flow, often suggesting malignancy or vascular lesion.
synonyms: adnexal tumor with high diastolic flow

22449.name: adrenal calcification
22449.description: Deposition of calcification in adrenal glands, usually a sequela of prior hemorrhage or infection.

22561.name: adrenal enlargement
22561.description: Adrenal gland larger than normal, may indicate hyperplasia, neoplasm, or infection.

17458.name: adrenal insufficiency
17458.description: A clinical condition where adrenal glands do not produce enough steroid hormones.

17441.name: adrenal pseudotumor
17441.description: Adrenal enlargement mimicking a tumor but caused by non-neoplastic processes, such as hyperplasia.

17436.name: adrenal tumor
17436.description: Mass lesion arising within the adrenal gland, can be benign or malignant.

22575.name: ambiguous genitalia
22575.description: Congenital condition where external genitalia do not have typical male or female appearance.

17623.name: anechoic prostate lesion
17623.description: Cystic or fluid-filled lesion within the prostate, appearing anechoic (dark) on ultrasound.

16942.name: anechoic renal mass
16942.description: A fluid-filled, echo-free mass in the kidney, often representing a simple cyst.

22601.name: anorchia
22601.description: Congenital absence of one or both testes.

17370.name: anterior urethral stricture
17370.description: Narrowing of the anterior urethra, usually from scarring, infection, or trauma.

16920.name: avascular renal mass
16920.description: A renal mass that lacks blood flow, often indicating a cyst or necrotic lesion.

22600.name: bifid scrotum
22600.description: Congenital anomaly resulting in a divided or cleft scrotum.

17424.name: bilateral adrenal enlargement
17424.description: Both adrenal glands are larger than expected; may suggest hyperplasia or infiltrative disease.

16360.name: bilateral large kidneys
16360.description: Both kidneys are larger than normal, which can be due to various processes including obstruction, infiltration, or congenital.

16668.name: bilateral or multiple cystic renal masses
16668.description: Presence of multiple fluid-filled masses in both kidneys, can indicate polycystic kidney disease or cystic neoplasms.

16316.name: bilateral small kidneys
16316.description: Both kidneys are smaller than expected, often due to chronic disease or congenital hypoplasia.

17687.name: bilateral testicular masses
17687.description: Presence of mass lesions in both testes, which may suggest lymphoma, metastases, or synchronous tumors.

16479.name: bilaterally decreased renal contrast concentration
16479.description: Reduced uptake of intravenous contrast in both kidneys, indicating impaired renal function or perfusion.

17328.name: bladder calculus
17328.description: A stone or calculus located within the urinary bladder.

17346.name: bladder diverticulum
17346.description: An outpouching or sac-like protrusion from the bladder wall.

22578.name: bladder dysfunction
22578.description: Impaired bladder function, such as neurogenic bladder or voiding difficulties.

17295.name: bladder filling defect
17295.description: An area within the bladder that fails to fill with contrast or urine, suggesting mass, clot or other lesion.

17289.name: bladder tumor
17289.description: A neoplastic mass arising from the bladder wall.

22580.name: bladder wall calcification
22580.description: Presence of calcifications within the bladder wall.

17314.name: calcification in bladder wall or lumen
17314.description: Calcified material located within the bladder wall or its lumen.

17762.name: calcifications in female genital tract
17762.description: Presence of calcified foci in the female reproductive organs.

17740.name: calcifications in scrotum
17740.description: Presence of calcified deposits within scrotal structures such as the testicle or tunica.

17851.name: cervical mass
17851.description: A mass lesion located in the uterine cervix.

16496.name: clubbing or destruction of renal calyces
16496.description: Deformity or loss of normal calyceal architecture, often due to chronic obstruction or infection.

17870.name: complex cystic adnexal mass
17870.description: A multilocular or septated cystic lesion associated with the adnexa, potentially neoplastic.

17556.name: complex pelvic mass
17556.description: A heterogeneous mass in the pelvic region that may involve several pelvic organs.

16650.name: congenital renal cystic disease
16650.description: A group of hereditary conditions leading to multiple cysts in one or both kidneys.

16234.name: congenital renal or ureteral anomaly
16234.description: Congenital malformation affecting the kidneys or ureters.

20518.name: cortical nephrocalcinosis
20518.description: Deposition of calcium in the renal cortex.

22584.name: cryptorchidism
22584.description: Undescended testicle, a congenital anomaly where one or both testes fail to descend into the scrotum.

17861.name: cystic adnexal mass
17861.description: A fluid-filled mass associated with the ovary or fallopian tube.

17431.name: cystic adrenal lesion
17431.description: A fluid-filled lesion in the adrenal gland, which can be benign or malignant.

17737.name: cystic extratesticular mass in scrotum
17737.description: A fluid-containing mass outside the testis, often arising from the epididymis or tunica vaginalis.

19091.name: cystic fetal mid-abdominal mass
19091.description: A fluid-filled mass in the mid-abdomen of a fetus, with broad differential diagnosis.

19094.name: cystic fetal pelvic mass
19094.description: A cystic lesion in the fetal pelvis, potentially deriving from urinary or reproductive organs.

17546.name: cystic pelvic mass
17546.description: A fluid-filled mass in the pelvic region which may arise from gynecologic, urinary, or gastrointestinal structures.

16773.name: cystic renal mass
16773.description: A fluid-filled lesion in the kidney that can be simple or complex.

16784.name: cystic renal mass with internal debris
16784.description: A kidney cystic mass containing internal echogenic material, which may indicate infection or neoplasm.

16789.name: cystic renal mass with wall calcification
16789.description: A renal cystic lesion with calcium deposition in its wall, which increases the suspicion for malignancy.

17507.name: cystic retroperitoneal mass
17507.description: A fluid-containing mass located in the retroperitoneal space.

17658.name: cystic structure near seminal vesicle
17658.description: A cystic lesion adjacent to the seminal vesicle, with possible congenital or acquired etiology.

17674.name: cystic testicular mass
17674.description: A fluid-filled lesion originating within the testicle.

17282.name: cystitis
17282.description: Inflammation of the urinary bladder, often due to infection.

16830.name: dark kidney on T2 MRI
16830.description: A kidney that appears hypointense on T2-weighted MRI sequences, associated with fibrosis or hemosiderosis.

16401.name: decreased nephrogram
16401.description: Reduced or delayed contrast enhancement of the kidney, often indicating impaired perfusion or obstruction.

17034.name: decreased renal artery diastolic flow
17034.description: Reduced diastolic blood flow in the renal artery, suggesting increased vascular resistance.

17002.name: decreased renal cortical echogenicity
17002.description: Lower than normal ultrasound reflectivity of the renal cortex, potentially indicating acute pathology.

17056.name: decreased renal transplant function
17056.description: Impaired performance of a transplanted kidney, which may be due to a variety of causes.

16291.name: decreased size of part of a kidney
16291.description: Atrophy or underdevelopment of a segment of a kidney.

16421.name: dense nephrogram
16421.description: Intense contrast enhancement of the kidney, frequently associated with decreased renal excretion.

16682.name: depression in renal margin
16682.description: An indentation or concavity in the kidney's outer contour, which can be congenital or acquired.

17794.name: diffusely enlarged uterus
17794.description: Uniform enlargement of the uterus due to a variety of causes.

17167.name: dilatation of ureter
17167.description: Abnormal widening of the ureter, often due to obstruction.

17376.name: dilated posterior urethra
17376.description: Enlargement of the posterior urethra, commonly associated with valve or obstruction.

17053.name: diminished size of renal transplant
17053.description: Renal transplant appears smaller than expected, possibly due to atrophy or rejection.

17106.name: displacement of pelvic ureter
17106.description: Ureter is abnormally shifted from its typical anatomical location.

16925.name: early renal vein opacification
16925.description: Venous phase of contrast appears early in the renal vein, suggestive of shunting or AV malformation.

17820.name: endometrial fluid
17820.description: Presence of fluid within the endometrial cavity.

17809.name: endometrial thickening
17809.description: Increased thickness of the endometrial lining of the uterus.

17620.name: enlarged prostate
17620.description: Increase in size of the prostate gland, commonly seen in benign prostatic hyperplasia.

22599.name: enlarged scrotum
22599.description: Increase in the overall size of the scrotal sac, can be due to multiple etiologies.

17049.name: enlargement of renal transplant
17049.description: Renal transplant is larger than expected, which may be seen in acute rejection or obstruction.

17711.name: epididymal lesion
17711.description: Abnormal focal lesion within the epididymis, can represent a cyst, tumor, or infection.

17728.name: extratesticular tumor in scrotum
17728.description: A neoplastic mass within the scrotum that is not originating from the testicle.

17248.name: extrinsic pressure deformity of bladder
17248.description: Bladder contour is distorted by pressure from an external structure or mass.
synonyms: bladder deformity due to external mass

21536.name: fallopian tube calcification
21536.description: Presence of calcified material within or along the fallopian tube.

17859.name: fallopian tube mass
17859.description: A mass lesion involving or arising from the fallopian tube.

16800.name: fat-containing renal mass
16800.description: A renal mass with macroscopic fat, most commonly representing angiomyolipoma.

16522.name: filling defect in renal collecting system
16522.description: A defect in contrast filling of the renal collecting system, may represent stone, tumor, or blood clot.

17753.name: fluid collection in scrotum
17753.description: Abnormal collection of fluid within the scrotal sac, e.g., hydrocele.

17269.name: focal bladder wall thickening
17269.description: Localized thickening of the bladder wall, may suggest neoplastic or inflammatory process.

16537.name: focal calcification in kidney
16537.description: Discrete area of calcification noted within the renal parenchyma.

16407.name: focal defect in nephrogram
16407.description: Localized area of decreased or absent contrast enhancement within the kidney on nephrogram phase.

16677.name: focal renal parenchymal scar
16677.description: Localized area of fibrosis or scarring in the renal cortex or medulla.

17854.name: free fluid in cul-de-sac
17854.description: Presence of non-physiologic fluid in the rectouterine pouch (pouch of Douglas).

17333.name: gas in bladder wall or lumen
17333.description: Presence of air or gas within the urinary bladder wall or cavity.

19116.name: gastroschisis
19116.description: Congenital defect with herniation of abdominal contents through the anterior abdominal wall.

17277.name: generalized bladder wall thickening
17277.description: Diffuse thickening of the urinary bladder wall.

22585.name: genital anomaly
22585.description: Structural abnormality of the genital organs, either internal or external.

17691.name: germ cell testicular tumor
17691.description: Neoplastic tumor arising from germ cells in the testis.

16674.name: high-density renal cyst
16674.description: Renal cyst with higher-than-simple cyst attenuation or signal.

22586.name: hypercalciuria
22586.description: Increased calcium in the urine, not a direct imaging finding.

17787.name: hyperechoic focal uterine lesion
17787.description: Localized area in the uterus with increased echogenicity.

17643.name: hyperechoic prostate lesion
17643.description: Prostate lesion appearing brighter than surrounding tissues on ultrasound.

17005.name: hyperechoic renal cortex
17005.description: Renal cortex that appears excessively echogenic on ultrasound.

16964.name: hyperechoic renal mass
16964.description: Discrete kidney mass with high echogenicity on ultrasound.

17016.name: hyperechoic renal medulla
17016.description: Medullary region of the kidney appears more echogenic on ultrasound.

17023.name: hyperechoic renal parenchyma
17023.description: Renal tissue is generally more echogenic than normal on ultrasound.

17646.name: hypervascular prostate lesion
17646.description: Prostate lesion with increased blood flow or contrast enhancement.

17632.name: hypoechoic prostate lesion
17632.description: Prostate lesion that appears darker than the surrounding tissue on ultrasound.

16953.name: hypoechoic renal mass
16953.description: Renal mass that is less echogenic than surrounding tissue on ultrasound.

22563.name: hypogonadism

22593.name: hypoplastic labia majora
22593.description: Underdevelopment of the labia majora, usually clinically evaluated.

22587.name: hypospadias
22587.description: Congenital anomaly where the urethral opening is located on the underside of the penis.

17756.name: hypospadias or ambiguous external genitalia
17756.description: Congenital genital anomaly involving abnormal position of urethral opening or undifferentiated genitalia.

17031.name: increased renal artery diastolic flow
17031.description: Blood flow signal in the renal artery showing abnormally high flow during diastole.

17041.name: increased resistance index of renal transplant
17041.description: Ultrasound Doppler measurement indicating higher resistance in renal transplant vasculature.

17833.name: indefinite uterus sign
17833.description: Indistinct visualization of the uterus, usually seen in pelvic imaging.

16510.name: infundibular narrowing
16510.description: Narrowing of the infundibulum, commonly of the renal collecting system.

17123.name: intraluminal ureteral filling defect
17123.description: A defect within the lumen of the ureter, often representing a stone, clot, or mass.

16489.name: intrarenal contrast collection
16489.description: Area of contrast accumulation within the kidney, often indicative of leakage or extravasation.

17640.name: isoechoic prostate lesion
17640.description: A prostate lesion that has the same echogenicity as surrounding tissue on ultrasound.

16960.name: isoechoic renal mass
16960.description: Renal mass that appears similar in echogenicity to the surrounding renal parenchyma.

22579.name: large bladder
22579.description: Distended urinary bladder, which may be due to retention or obstruction.

22591.name: large kidney
22591.description: Enlargement of the kidney relative to age- or sex-matched norms.

16393.name: large kidneys with multifocal masses
16393.description: Both kidneys are enlarged and contain multiple masses, suggestive of infiltrative or neoplastic disease.

17520.name: large pelvic soft-tissue mass
17520.description: A sizable abnormal soft tissue lesion within the pelvic cavity.

22597.name: large penis
22597.description: Penis larger than expected for age or normal size range.

17094.name: lateral deviation of upper ureter
17094.description: Displacement of the upper segment of the ureter toward the lateral direction.

16832.name: lesion of perinephric space
16832.description: Abnormality observed in the space around the kidney, may represent fluid, blood, or tumor.

16689.name: localized bulge of renal outline
16689.description: A focal protrusion or contour abnormality of the renal surface.

17580.name: lower abdominal calcification
17580.description: Presence of calcified material in the lower abdominal region detectable on imaging.

22603.name: macroorchidism
22603.description: Abnormally enlarged testes, can be congenital or acquired.

22594.name: male megalourethra
22594.description: A rare congenital anomaly characterized by abnormal dilation of the male urethra.

16261.name: malposition of kidney
16261.description: Abnormal location or position of the kidney outside its usual anatomical area.

16273.name: mass displacing kidney

17716.name: mass in scrotum
17716.description: Any abnormal soft tissue mass located within the scrotal sac.

17083.name: medial deviation of upper ureter
17083.description: Abnormal inward deviation of the upper ureter toward the midline.

20215.name: medullary nephrocalcinosis
20215.description: Deposition of calcium in the renal medulla.

22604.name: microorchidism
22604.description: Abnormally small testes, often related to genetic or metabolic syndromes.

22598.name: micropenis
22598.description: A penis significantly shorter than the normal length for age and stage of development.

16978.name: multilocular or complex renal mass
16978.description: Renal mass with multiple compartments separated by septa, often with solid and cystic components.

16660.name: multiloculated cystic renal lesion
16660.description: Renal cystic lesion featuring multiple loculated compartments.

17148.name: multiple ureteral filling defects

17133.name: mural ureteral filling defect

16754.name: neonatal renal mass
16754.description: A mass lesion of the kidney detected in a neonate.

31828.name: nephroblastomatosis

3303.name: nephrocalcinosis

31829.name: nephrogenic rests

16247.name: nephropathy

17695.name: non-germ cell testicular tumor

16463.name: nonfunction of part of kidney
16463.description: Absence of normal function in a portion of the kidney, often seen as lack of contrast uptake or tracer activity.

17187.name: obstruction of ureter
17187.description: Blockage of urine flow within the ureter leading to upstream dilatation.

25402.name: ovarian cyst
25402.description: A fluid-filled sac within or on the ovary.

19199.name: ovarian mass in pregnancy
19199.description: Presence of a mass in the ovary during pregnancy, which may be benign or malignant.

17894.name: ovarian neoplasm or cyst in a child
17894.description: Presence of a neoplastic or cystic lesion of the ovary in a pediatric patient.

25403.name: ovarian tumor
25403.description: A neoplastic mass arising from the ovary; may be benign or malignant.

17566.name: pelvic mass in an infant or child
17566.description: Any abnormal mass detected in the pelvis of a pediatric patient.

16854.name: perinephric hematoma
16854.description: A collection of blood in the space around the kidney, often due to trauma.

16868.name: peripelvic extravasation
16868.description: Leakage of urine or contrast into the space around the renal pelvis.

16874.name: peripheral rim enhancement of kidney

16841.name: perirenal fluid collection
16841.description: Presence of fluid surrounding the kidney, which may represent urine, blood, or exudate.

17466.name: pheochromocytoma

19136.name: polyhydramnios

22565.name: precocious puberty

17837.name: prominence of central uterine echo

22566.name: pseudohermaphroditism

16908.name: renal artery aneurysm or microaneurysm

17027.name: renal collecting system echoes

16635.name: renal cystic disease

16815.name: renal hemorrhage

16879.name: renal ischemia

16741.name: renal mass in a child

16793.name: renal mass with calcification
16793.description: A renal mass containing areas of calcification.

16502.name: renal papillary necrosis
16502.description: Necrosis of the renal papillae, often associated with infection or vascular compromise.

16821.name: renal parenchymal gas
16821.description: Presence of gas within the kidney parenchyma, usually indicating infection.

16728.name: renal parenchymal tumor

16698.name: renal pseudotumor

16931.name: renal vein thrombosis

4270.name: right anterior pararenal space abscess
4270.description: A localized collection of pus in the right anterior pararenal space.

22581.name: scrotal calcification
22581.description: Presence of calcified foci within the scrotal contents.

21535.name: seminal vesicle calcification
21535.description: Calcium deposits within the seminal vesicles.

16996.name: shadowing mass in renal collecting system
16996.description: A mass in the renal collecting system that causes acoustic shadowing on ultrasound.

17224.name: small bladder

22592.name: small kidney
22592.description: A kidney that is smaller than expected for age or body habitus.

22576.name: small urinary bladder
22576.description: Diminutive urinary bladder size or capacity.

17734.name: solid extratesticular mass in scrotum
17734.description: A solid mass located outside the testis within the scrotal sac.

17886.name: solid ovarian tumor

17534.name: solid pelvic mass

16758.name: solid renal mass

17671.name: solid testicular mass

16993.name: sonographically ill-defined renal parenchymal mass
16993.description: A renal mass with indistinct margins identified on ultrasound imaging.

16443.name: striated nephrogram

18938.name: T1-hyperintense adnexal mass

18855.name: T1-hyperintense adrenal mass

18890.name: T1-hyperintense endometrial uterine mass

18912.name: T1-hyperintense myometrial uterine mass

18953.name: T1-hyperintense prostate mass

18872.name: T1-hyperintense renal mass
18872.description: Renal lesion demonstrating increased signal on T1-weighted MRI, usually indicating hemorrhage or fat.

17654.name: T2-dark seminal vesicle

18917.name: T2-hyperintense adnexal mass
18917.description: Adnexal lesion with high T2 signal, often indicating cystic or fluid-filled content.

18847.name: T2-hyperintense adrenal mass
18847.description: Adrenal lesion with markedly increased signal on T2-weighted sequences, common in pheochromocytomas or cystic masses.

18876.name: T2-hyperintense endometrial uterine mass

18897.name: T2-hyperintense myometrial uterine mass
18897.description: A myometrial lesion in the uterus that is hyperintense on T2-weighted MRI, often seen in leiomyomas with edema or cystic degeneration.

18945.name: T2-hyperintense prostate mass
18945.description: A prostate lesion with high T2 signal, often associated with benign or cystic processes.

18863.name: T2-hyperintense renal mass

18932.name: T2-hypointense adnexal mass
18932.description: An adnexal mass that appears dark on T2-weighted MRI, may indicate a fibrous or solid neoplasm.

18885.name: T2-hypointense endometrial uterine mass
18885.description: A mass in the endometrial region of the uterus appearing dark on T2-weighted MRI, which may be due to fibrous tissue or hemorrhage.

18908.name: T2-hypointense myometrial uterine mass
18908.description: Myometrial lesion showing low signal on T2-weighted MRI, often indicative of fibrous or solid tumor such as a leiomyoma.

17649.name: T2-hypointense peripheral zone of prostate

18950.name: T2-hypointense prostate mass

18869.name: T2-hypointense renal mass

18852.name: T2-intermediate adrenal mass
18852.description: Adrenal mass with intermediate T2 signal intensity on MRI.

18883.name: T2-intermediate endometrial uterine mass
18883.description: Uterine mass arising from the endometrium with intermediate T2-weighted MRI signal.

18904.name: T2-intermediate myometrial uterine mass

18859.name: T2-intermediate renal mass

22602.name: testicular anomaly

17703.name: testicular calcification

17701.name: testicular tumor in a child

16282.name: unilateral absence or blurring of renal outline

16341.name: unilateral large kidney

16301.name: unilateral small kidney

17680.name: unilateral testicular tumor

16470.name: unilaterally decreased renal contrast concentration

17115.name: ureteral and renal pelvic calcification

17206.name: ureteral extravasation or fistula

17142.name: ureteral tumor

17400.name: urethral outpouching

17380.name: urethral tumor

16552.name: urinary tract calculus

22605.name: uterine anomaly

22606.name: vaginal anomaly

17752.name: vas deferens calcification

17156.name: vascular indentation on ureter or renal pelvis
